The Members of the Welsh Assembly (AM, for their English acronym) are worried about "looking like muppets"
Some Members of the Assembly are perplexed by the suggestion that their title should be changed to Members of the Welsh Parliament (MWP, for its English acronym).
This confusion arises from the plans to change the name of the Welsh Assembly to the Welsh Parliament.
Members of the whole political spectrum are concerned that this could be ridiculed.
A Member of the Labour Party stated that his group was concerned "that it would stay with Twp and Pwp."
For the readers outside of Wales: In Welsh, twp means stupid and pwp means shit.
A Member of the Welsh Assembly commented that the whole group was "dissatisfied" and has suggested alternatives.
A member of the Conservative Party of Wales stated that their group was "open" to a name change, but noted that the change from MWP to muppet was "small."
In this context, the pronunciation of the letter w in Welsh is similar to the pronunciation of the letter u in English from Yorkshire.
The Commission of the Assembly, which is currently drafting the legislation to introduce the change of name, states: "Of course, the final decision on any descriptive element of the name of the Members of the Assembly will be a matter for the Members themselves."
In 2017, the Government of Wales Act gave the Assembly of Wales the power to change its name.
In June, the Commission published the results of a public consultation on the proposals which revealed widespread support for calling the National Assembly for Wales to Parliament.
On the question of the title of Members of the Assembly, the Commission preferred Members of the Parliament of Wales (or WMP), but the option MWP got the most support in a public consultation.
Apparently, the Members of the Assembly are suggesting alternatives, but the struggle to reach a consensus could bring down the President of the Assembly, Elin Jones, who would have to send the bill for the changes in a few weeks.
The legislation on the reforms will include other changes related to the functioning of the assembly, such as rules on the disqualification of members and the design of the committee system.
The members of the Assembly will have the last word on how they should be called when the Assembly deliberates on the legislation.
