Zoran Zaev, Prime Minister of Macedonia, his wife Zorica and their son Dushko deposited their vote in the referendum of Macedonia on a change of name of the country that would open the way for the country to join NATO and the EU in Strumica (Macedonia) on September 30, 2018.
