"Denies this information with anger," wrote Fleischer.
This suggests a lack of the necessary temperance to be a Member of Congress.
When someone is accused of something they didn't do, they shouldn't get angry.
Don't rebel.
The defendant should not question the motives of the accuser.
He must maintain his calm and serenity.
